		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001046_0001"/><!--pb/@n='57r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><placeName>Barnet</placeName> 20<hi rend="sup">th</hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>June 1857 </p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I enclose a letter 
<lb/>from Holland. I know 
<lb/>nothing of the writer 
<lb/>except what it contains<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>As you are 
<lb/>acquainted with 
<lb/><persName>Sir G. Wilkinson</persName>
<lb/>would it be 
<w>con-<lb break="no"/>venient</w>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001046_0002"/><!--pb/@n='57v'--> 
<lb/>to ask him for me 
<lb/>about the crooked 
<lb/>stick or leg - which 
<lb/>is common 
<lb/>through all the 
<lb/>central country of 
<lb/><placeName>Africa</placeName> as an 
<lb/>object of worship<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>When the natives 
<lb/>refer to their 
<lb/>god they all 
<lb/>speak of him 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001046_0003"/><!--pb/@n='58r'--> 
<lb/>with only one leg 
<lb/>or a crooked one. 
<lb/>Now I have the 
<lb/>impression that 
<lb/>Thoth was supposed 
<lb/>to lame or 
<lb/>something of 
<lb/>that sort and 
<lb/>looking into 
<lb/>the Ancient Egyptians 
<lb/>to be certain I 
<lb/>do not find the impression 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001046_0004"/><!--pb/@n='58v'--> 
<lb/>verified. I should 
<lb/>like if convenient 
<lb/>to ask <persName>Sir G. 
<lb/>Wilkinson</persName> about it<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>I am &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>D. Livingstone</persName></p>
			
</div>
